	<div id="lead-row-copy-frame">
		<div id="lead-row-header">
							<h1>Bloody Sunday</h1> 
								</div>

		<div id="lead-row-copy">
			<p><p>On 30 January 1972, a civil rights demonstration through the streets of Londonderry in north-west Northern Ireland ended with the shooting dead of thirteen civilians by the British Army.</p>
<br />
<p>An official government inquiry began two weeks later but was widely considered a whitewash, leading to a fresh public inquiry in 1998 that took 12 years to report and absolved the victims of blame.</p>
<br />
<p>Explore the history of Bloody Sunday with over 40 years of BBC archive clips.</p>
<br />
<p>Photo: Demonstrators on a civil rights march through the streets of Londonderry before the shootings on Bloody Sunday</p></p>

					</div>

			</div>

</div>

<div id="secondary-rows">
	
<script type="text/Javascript"> 
			var RESOURCE_CLIPS_URI = null;
	 

			var RESOURCE_AUDIO_URI = null;
	 
</script>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-a">

			
				<div class="box">
	<div class="box-heading">
        <h2>Timeline of key events: details and archive clips</h2>
	</div>
    <div class="box-content">
    	

		<ul class="thmbLinksLrg" id="tll-events">
		
